---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import PageLayout from "@/layouts/Base.astro";
import profile from "@/assets/profile.jpg";
---

<PageLayout meta={{ title: "Oscar Gilg" }}>
	<section class="space-y-5">
		<div class="flex flex-col-reverse items-start gap-6 sm:flex-row sm:gap-8">
			<div class="flex-1 space-y-4">
				<h1 class="title">Oscar Gilg</h1>
				<p class="leading-relaxed">
					I work on empirical AI welfare research at MATS 9.0, mentored by
					<a class="cactus-link" href="https://patrickbutlin.com/" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank"
						>Patrick Butlin</a
					>.
				</p>
			</div>
			<Image
				alt="Oscar Gilg"
				class="border-accent/30 aspect-square w-32 shrink-0 rounded-full border-2 object-cover shadow-sm sm:w-40"
				loading="eager"
				src={profile}
				width={400}
				widths={[160, 240, 320, 480]}
			/>
		</div>
		<p class="leading-relaxed">
			I started getting interested in AI as a teenager when I realised that the human brain
			wasn't anything more than a computer. I read <em>Superintelligence</em> by Nick
			Bostrom and thought it all sounded very fascinating, but when I learned about CNNs and
			modern ML I thought there was really no way this stuff was going to happen within the
			timelines predicted at the start of the book (they turned out to be pretty decent!). So
			during Covid I started reading about my new favourite topic: consciousness.
			<em>Consciousness Explained</em> by Daniel Dennett, along with
			<em>From Bacteria to Bach and Back</em>, is how I really grokked the idea that bottom-up
			processes can be pretty powerful and lead to surprising emergent properties. You'd think I
			would catch onto AI and scaling laws, but instead I got pretty interested in another kind
			of bottom-up process: markets. It was pretty clear to me after an internship at Optiver
			that all the smartest people I knew were going into trading. So I (as a good trader)
			followed the flow, with a quick pit-stop in Bochum to work with the fantastic
			<a
				class="cactus-link"
				href="https://www.francoiskammerer.com/"
				rel="noreferrer"
				target="_blank">François Kammerer</a
			> on the best theory of consciousness: illusionism.
		</p>
		<p class="leading-relaxed">
			So I moved to Amsterdam. Got my first paycheck, immediately bought a boat. Learned a bit of Dutch and a lot about life.
			Trading teaches you a lot, especially when you're surrounded by very smart people. But when
			o3 came out it became clear to me the world was going to change, and that this intuition I
			had back when I was 17 was actually maybe worth acting on.
		</p>
		<p class="leading-relaxed">
			So I left trading, applied to MATS, and started doing empirical AI welfare research. Lucky
			for me, all that consciousness reading turns out to be useful as we try to make sense of
			what we are creating.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="mt-12">
		<h2 class="title text-accent mb-4 text-xl">Projects</h2>
		<ul class="space-y-4" role="list">
			<li>
				<div class="flex items-baseline justify-between gap-4">
					<a
						class="cactus-link font-semibold"
						href="https://github.com/oscar-gilg/zombuul"
						rel="noreferrer"
						target="_blank">Zombuul</a
					>
					<span class="text-muted shrink-0 text-xs">2026</span>
				</div>
				<p class="text-muted mt-1">
					I built a Claude Code plugin for launching autonomous research agents with access to
					GPUs.
				</p>
			</li>
			<li>
				<div class="flex items-baseline justify-between gap-4">
					<span class="font-semibold">Personas use a shared preference vector</span>
					<span class="text-muted shrink-0 text-xs">MATS 9.0, 2026</span>
				</div>
				<p class="text-muted mt-1">
					With Patrick Butlin (
					<a
						class="cactus-link"
						href="https://www.lesswrong.com/posts/pxC2RAeoBrvK8ivMf/models-have-linear-representations-of-what-tasks-they-like-1"
						rel="noreferrer"
						target="_blank">post</a
					>,
					<a
						class="cactus-link"
						href="https://github.com/oscar-gilg/Preferences"
						rel="noreferrer"
						target="_blank">code</a
					>; preprint forthcoming).
				</p>
			</li>
			<li>
				<div class="flex items-baseline justify-between gap-4">
					<span class="font-semibold">Split Persona Training</span>
					<span class="text-muted shrink-0 text-xs">SPAR 2025</span>
				</div>
				<p class="text-muted mt-1">
					Trigger-conditioned persona fine-tuning. Under review at ICML 2026.
				</p>
			</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section class="mt-12">
		<h2 class="title text-accent mb-4 text-xl">CV</h2>
		<p>
			<a class="cactus-link" href="/cv.pdf" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank">View CV (PDF)</a>
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="mt-12">
		<h2 class="title text-accent mb-4 text-xl">Contact</h2>
		<ul class="list-disc space-y-1 ps-5" role="list">
			<li>
				Email:
				<span data-email-user="oscar.gilg18" data-email-domain="gmail.com"
					>oscar.gilg18 [at] gmail [dot] com</span
				>
			</li>
			<li>
				<a
					class="cactus-link"
					href="https://github.com/oscar-gilg"
					rel="noreferrer"
					target="_blank">github.com/oscar-gilg</a
				>
			</li>
			<li>
				<a
					class="cactus-link"
					href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/oscar-gilg"
					rel="noreferrer"
					target="_blank">linkedin.com/in/oscar-gilg</a
				>
			</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<script is:inline>
		document.querySelectorAll("[data-email-user]").forEach(function (el) {
			var u = el.getAttribute("data-email-user");
			var d = el.getAttribute("data-email-domain");
			var addr = u + "@" + d;
			var a = document.createElement("a");
			a.href = "mai" + "lto:" + addr;
			a.textContent = addr;
			a.className = "cactus-link";
			el.replaceWith(a);
		});
	</script>
</PageLayout>
